# This superproject is a thin workspace bootstrapper: it tracks only its own
# files. Every member repo is cloned in by ./bootstrap.sh and must stay ignored
# so `git status` here is unaffected by their state — and so there are no
# submodule pointers to bump. Ignore everything at the root, then re-include the
# handful of files this repo actually owns. New repos added to the catalog and
# cloned in are ignored automatically, with no edit here.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/.claude
!/README.md
!/bootstrap.sh
!/CONVENTIONS.md
!/ACCESSIBILITY.md
